parameters.description: Log maximum fold-increase in larval survival during high nutrient conditions (e.g., flood-driven phytoplankton blooms)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log maximum enhancement of larval survival during nutrient-rich conditions. exp(1.609)=5x baseline survival (range 2x to 20x). Captures episodic recruitment pulses during flood events that trigger COTS outbreaks.

parameters.description: Log SST anomaly threshold at which nutrient-mediated larval survival enhancement reaches half its maximum (proxy for nutrient pulse intensity)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log temperature anomaly for half-maximal nutrient effect. exp(0.693)=2°C anomaly. Represents threshold for significant nutrient-driven recruitment enhancement. Lower values = more sensitive to warm/wet conditions.

parameters.description: Hill coefficient controlling steepness of nutrient-mediated larval survival response
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Exponent for nutrient response curve steepness. Higher values create sharper threshold behavior, capturing the episodic nature of outbreak-triggering nutrient pulses. Typical range 2-4 for ecological threshold responses.

parameters.description: Log maximum fold-increase in per-capita fecundity at high COTS density due to aggregation and improved fertilization success
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log maximum fecundity enhancement during outbreaks (exp(1.609)=5x baseline, range 2x to 20x). Captures density-dependent fertilization success in broadcast spawners.

parameters.description: Log COTS density at which density-dependent fecundity enhancement reaches half its maximum value
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log half-saturation density for fecundity response (exp(-0.693)=0.5 ind/m²). Determines density threshold for outbreak-level reproduction.

parameters.description: Hill coefficient controlling steepness of density-dependent fecundity response
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Exponent for fecundity response curve (higher values = sharper transition). Typical range 2-4 for cooperative biological processes.
